      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROCKY GALVIN (1) produced a moderate performance last time when seventh at this track over 300m behind Golden Effects (18.44) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Looks the one to beat on his best form. LOST COMPASS (2) was safely held last time out, finishing seventh at The Gardens over 400m behind Hooked On Hope (24.06) in a Grade 5. Has a strong record from box 2, including two wins. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. NOAH'S OWN (8) has been out of the placings the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner (17.82) three back at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can find the frame this time. CHICKS A THIEF (3) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
